      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 148: The comment says inputs are clamped to prevent NaN pollution, but `std::clamp`/`std::max` do not sanitize NaN values reliably. A NaN RTCP metric can permanently poison EWMA state and all future congestion decisions. Explicitly reject non-finite samples before updating the controller.\n```suggestion\n    if (!std::isfinite(packetLoss) || !std::isfinite(jitterMs) || !std::isfinite(rttMs)) {\n        JAMI_WARNING(\"[BandwidthCtrl] Ignoring non-finite RTCP sample: loss\u003d{} jitter\u003d{} rtt\u003d{}\",\n                     packetLoss,\n                     jitterMs,\n                     rttMs);\n        return targetBitrate_;\n    }\n\n    packetLoss \u003d std::clamp(packetLoss, 0.0f, 100.0f);\n    jitterMs \u003d std::max(jitterMs, 0.0f);\n    rttMs \u003d std::max(rttMs, 0.0f);\n```",
      "revId": "310544f7c9717eaa4f069804a2f38b3aee02cf6d",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
