      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 655: REMB bitrate units appear to be mishandled. `check_RCTP_Info_REMB()` returns the REMB bitrate field, which is normally in bits per second, but this branch treats values below 100000 as Kbps and passes them directly to `setTargetBitrate()`/`setNewBitrate()`. A 64 Kbps REMB estimate would be interpreted as 64000 Kbps and clamped to max, increasing bitrate under congestion instead of reducing it. Convert real REMB estimates to Kbps before applying them, and keep sentinel handling separate.\n```suggestion\n        } else if (br \u003e 0) {\n            auto rembKbps \u003d static_cast\u003cunsigned\u003e(br / 1000);\n            auto currentBitrate \u003d bwController_.getTargetBitrate();\n            if (rembKbps \u003e 0 \u0026\u0026 rembKbps \u003c currentBitrate) {\n                bwController_.setTargetBitrate(rembKbps);\n                setNewBitrate(rembKbps);\n            }\n        }\n```",
      "revId": "310544f7c9717eaa4f069804a2f38b3aee02cf6d",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
