      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 673: The post-restart RTCP guard returns from `adaptQualityAndBitrate()` entirely when an RR report arrives within 2 seconds. Because REMB is processed before this block, that may be acceptable for the current ordering, but this early return also skips any future logic added after RR processing and makes the function fragile. Prefer skipping only the stale RR sample.\n```suggestion\n        if (sinceRestart \u003e\u003d 2.0f) {\n#if !__ANDROID__\n            if (rtcpi.jitter \u003c\u003d 1000)\n#endif\n            {\n                auto newBitrate \u003d bwController_.update(rtcpi.packetLoss,\n                                                       static_cast\u003cfloat\u003e(rtcpi.jitter),\n                                                       rtcpi.latency);\n                setNewBitrate(newBitrate);\n            }\n        }\n```",
